The paper describes a hardware-efficient on-line learning technique for feedforward multi-layer ANNs that is based on pipelined backpropagation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with hardware implementation of ANNs, which could also place it in the sub-categories of Architecture (cs.AR) and Emerging Technologies (cs.ET). The paper also discusses the performance of the technique on the MNIST handwritten digit classification dataset, which could place it in the sub-categories of Learning (cs.LG) and Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV).
